# Git Workflow

## Branch Naming

`feature/<slug>`, `fix/<slug>` (e.g. `feature/add-instance-settings`)

Same slug across repos for cross-platform features.

## Commits

**Format**: `<category>: [Tag] <description>`

**Categories**: feature, bug, chore, docs, refactor, test

**Tags** (square brackets, optional): `[CI]` `[Core]` `[API]` `[Docs]`

- In this repo, **do not use `[iOS]`** — it's implicit.
- Use tags only when helpful; omit for small, obvious changes.

**Examples:**
- `chore: [CI] add iOS CI pipeline`
- `feature: add instance list screen`
- `bug: fix crash on search`

## Polyrepo Commits

When changes affect multiple repos, commit in each affected repo separately. See mono `git-commit-pr.mdc` for full guidance (commit format, PR, polyrepo). See `git-core.mdc` for safety.

Do not push unless explicitly asked. Local commits only.

## PR

- Fill template (description, type, checklist)
- Link related PRs in other repos
- Squash merge after review
